From: Tang Yuantian <Yuantian.Tang@nxp.com>
Date: Wed, 21 Sep 2016 14:03:48 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 052/388] sata: ls1021a: update clock property in sata node

ls1021a uses the legacy clock structure, so for sata,
it should use legacy clock property too.

Signed-off-by: Tang Yuantian <yuantian.tang@nxp.com>
[Original patch taken from SDK-V2.0-1703]
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/ls1021a.dtsi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/ls1021a.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/ls1021a.dtsi
index d544710..b9b7418 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/ls1021a.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/ls1021a.dtsi
@@ -175,7 +175,7 @@
 			      <0x0 0x20220520 0x0 0x4>;
 			reg-names = "ahci", "sata-ecc";
 			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 101 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
-			clocks = <&clockgen 4 1>;
+			clocks = <&platform_clk 1>;
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
